# PowerUp Landing Page - Environment Variables Example
# 
# Copy this file to .env.local (for Next.js) or use your hosting platform's
# environment variable settings.

# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard:
# Settings > API

# Your Supabase project URL
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url

# Your Supabase anonymous/public API key
# This is the "anon public" key from the API settings
# It's safe to use in frontend code with proper RLS policies
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# Optional: Additional configuration

# Google Analytics ID (if using)
# GA_TRACKING_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Email notification webhook URL (if using)
# NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.zapier.com/...

# Notes:
# - Never commit .env files with real values to version control
# - Add .env.local to your .gitignore file
# - For GitHub Pages, use GitHub Secrets and replace values during build
# - For Netlify/Vercel, add these in the dashboard environment variables section
